    4.0 out of 5 starsNice Lightweight Windbreaker Shell With Modest Water Resistance - Excellent Packable Backup Coat
    ByMr. Staackon December 1, 2017
    Size: XX-Large|Color: Black|Verified Purchase
    Very light windbreaker outer shell, with modest water resistance. After some wear, the water resistance might need a little touch-up (I recommend Kiwi brand waterproofing spray). Has almost no thermal insulative properties, so it is best paired with a warmer under layer. Dries quickly, and easily loses wrinkles, with simply hanging on a coat hanger for a half hour. It won't replace a real rain coat, but it's still a nice backup option that's very easily packable in a small space and a lot more comfortable than a disposable poncho.

    Bycody bleileon June 27, 2015
    Size: Large|Color: Navy Blue|Verified Purchase
    I like this Jacket. It is a simple basic jacket for a light rainy or windy day. However it does fit a little too large for my liking, the arm length is perfect, but the body of the jacket is somewhat large. If you are a heavy outdoors person and think you might find yourself in a down pour, I would not recommend this jacket. If you are going to a event or waiting for the bus and don't like carrying a umbrella, this jacket is perfect.

    for sizing reference, I am a 5'11" 175lb male.
